title: I’m at a loss
body:
So, this has made the countdown for SiriusXM Hits 1 Weekend Countdown at #39, yet, Two of Us isn’t even on the list.  I feel like a failure at this point.

Here is the review of the song (thankfully, spot on)

~ We have seven entries this week including one re-entry. We’ll go from worst to best starting with what could possibly be one of the worst songs of 2019. It is Harry by Kelsy Karter. I don’t know where Hits 1 found this song, but it’s honestly just horrendous. I want to think this song is some kind of joke because this is one of the most obnoxious things I’ve heard in a while. Apparently this song is about Harry Styles, which just makes the song so weird when reading through the lyrics. It probably wouldn’t be as weird if she didn’t name the song after him. And her vocals here are awful. Her screaming in the chorus is hard to listen to and I don’t really like her voice in the verses. Overall, this song is just more annoying than anything else and I don’t understand why it’s here. I hope it doesn’t stick around very long.

I just can’t believe a song that glorifies stalking and an unhealthy obsession beats out a song that holds some much meaning for so many different people in the world.

Posting various random writings I've written over the years. Mixture of One Direction & 5SOS

M A S T E R L I S T

body:
Don’t get me wrong…

I love seeing hontent, especially since we’ve been getting so much of it lately…but sometimes when I see pics of harry out to eat, at the supermarket, at an exhibit, I’m like…seriously ?? He can’t even enjoy an art exhibit without his pic being taken ? Or without someone asking for a pic ??

Idk maybe this is just my unpopular opinion but I think people forget he’s human too. I mean how would y’all feel about popping into a store for something quick and people all of a sudden hounding you for a pic when all you need to do is buy some milk ?? Why can’t we ever just let celebrities live their lives ?
